    <section>
      <h2>About Vypin</h2>
      <p>
        At the northern tip of Vypin lies Munambam Fishing Harbour, the largest in Kochi. Puthuvype has become a key
        industrial hub with major facilities like the LNG Terminal, IOC Bottling Plant, and the upcoming Oceanarium.
      </p>
      <p>
        One of Kerala’s ten lighthouses stands at Puthuvype Beach—the tallest in the state—adding charm to its coastline.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="https://www.bing.com/search?q=ABOUT+VYPIN" target="_blank">Know More</a>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>History of Vypin</h2>
      <p><strong>Early Days:</strong> In the 16th century, the Portuguese built a fort on Vypin with the permission of the Raja of Kochi. 
        This marked the start of European colonialism in the region.</p>
      <p>
        With its serene beaches like Cherai and easy access to Kochi city, Vypin slowly became a tourist hotspot for those seeking peace.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Modern Growth:</strong> Improved ferry services and the Goshree bridges helped boost tourism. Sustainable development 
        supports eco-tourism, preserving local ecosystems while attracting visitors.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="https://travelsetu.com/guide/vypin-island-tourism/vypin-island-tourism-history" target="_blank">Know More</a>
    </section>

